to collect fees. The Arroyo did both.

The "unpaid names" haunt the Temple Circle most -- dead whose rites
were withheld pending debt settlement, souls in administrative
suspension. In Kowloon, the Ashfall Registry exists because six
hundred drowned in Yen-Mak and the survivors swore every death
would be named. The unpaid names are a violation of the most basic
compact between living and dead.

