declarations -- are registry without registrar. The Courier Lantern
Office classifies these as signal echoes: institutional patterns
repeating after the institution has died. Canyon walls carry
overwritten inscriptions. The Jade Magistracy calls this palimpsest
governance. Kowloon's terraced stone carries the same layers -- but
we read ours.

The Arroyo's water-debt system is horrifyingly familiar: our own
harbor licensing stripped of mercy, accountability, and sunset. The
Arroyo is not a foreign horror. It is a local possibility --
the version of Kowloon that forgot why the lanterns were lit.
